    },
    "MissionGiver": "Crusader Industries",
    "Title": "RESOURCE DRIVE: LARGE CARGO SHIP RECOVERY",
    "TitleKey": "GoblinG_Crusader_RecoverCargo_L_Title",
    "Description": "One of our contractors, who was due to deliver a large shipment of cargo for us, has been forced to abandon their ship at <EM4>~mission(Location|Address)</EM4>.\n\nTrackers are indicating that the cargo is still intact, but we\u2019ve been unable to contact the pilot. We have reason to suspect there may be hostile forces onsite. We\u2019re looking for a pilot with a large hauling ship to head out there and bring the cargo back.\n\nThese resources are crucial to helping us win the UEE\u2019s incentive program, so try to recover as much as possible. Expect to find between <EM4>100-125 SCU</EM4> of various box sizes. You\u2019ll need <EM4>a heavy-duty tractor beam</EM4> to move it. If you are unable to retrieve all of it, we can only offer a partial payment for what you bring us. <EM4>We highly recommend bringing back-up for this one</EM4>, for your own sake.\n\nOnce obtained, take the cargo to a freight elevator at: <EM4>~mission(Destination|Address|ListAll)</EM4>. We\u2019ll take care of the rest.\n\nWhen you find the deserted ship, if you think you or your co-pilot would be able to fly it back instead of extracting the cargo, that might be easier for you.\n\nBe safe out there.\n\n\nDenver Samuels\nContractor Liaison Officer\nCrusader Industries",
    "DescriptionKey": "GoblinG_Crusader_RecoverCargo_L_Desc",
    "DisplayDescription": "One of our contractors, who was due to deliver a large shipment of cargo for us, has been forced to abandon their ship at <EM4>[Location|Address]</EM4>.\n\nTrackers are indicating that the cargo is still intact, but we\u2019ve been unable to contact the pilot. We have reason to suspect there may be hostile forces onsite. We\u2019re looking for a pilot with a large hauling ship to head out there and bring the cargo back.\n\nThese resources are crucial to helping us win the UEE\u2019s incentive program, so try to recover as much as possible. Expect to find between <EM4>100-125 SCU</EM4> of various box sizes. You\u2019ll need <EM4>a heavy-duty tractor beam</EM4> to move it. If you are unable to retrieve all of it, we can only offer a partial payment for what you bring us. <EM4>We highly recommend bringing back-up for this one</EM4>, for your own sake.\n\nOnce obtained, take the cargo to a freight elevator at: <EM4>Orison</EM4>. We\u2019ll take care of the rest.\n\nWhen you find the deserted ship, if you think you or your co-pilot would be able to fly it back instead of extracting the cargo, that might be easier for you.\n\nBe safe out there.\n\n\nDenver Samuels\nContractor Liaison Officer\nCrusader Industries",
